WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:03:10.250 --> 00:03:15.690
Today we have decided to have a Hamsa Puja in Germany.

00:03:21.850 --> 00:03:24.790
We have never yet

00:03:24.930 --> 00:03:28.570
paid much attention to this center of Hamsa,

00:03:28.770 --> 00:03:33.250
which is, I think, very important for the Western world,

00:03:33.430 --> 00:03:37.730
rather than for the Indian or the Eastern.

00:03:37.990 --> 00:03:43.130
The reason is, at the Hamsa chakra,

00:03:43.530 --> 00:03:47.710
part of the Ida and Pingala

00:03:49.270 --> 00:03:52.690
come out and manifest.

00:03:53.470 --> 00:03:58.010
Means, the expression

00:03:58.750 --> 00:04:03.110
of Ida and Pingala is given through the Hamsa chakra.

00:04:03.970 --> 00:04:09.270
So this Hamsa chakra is the one

00:04:09.990 --> 00:04:14.910
that, as if has not gone

00:04:16.770 --> 00:04:19.690
up to the Agya,

00:04:19.870 --> 00:04:23.730
but is holding on certain threads

00:04:23.910 --> 00:04:29.430
or certain parts of the Ida and Pingala.

00:04:31.910 --> 00:04:35.310
And they start flowing through your nose,

00:04:35.490 --> 00:04:39.150
expressing through your eyes, from your mouth

00:04:39.330 --> 00:04:42.430
and from your forehead.

00:04:42.630 --> 00:04:46.010
So you know that Vishuddhi chakra

00:04:46.190 --> 00:04:49.790
has got sixteen petals,

00:04:50.270 --> 00:04:54.390
which look after the eyes,

00:04:54.570 --> 00:04:59.390
nose, throat, tongue, teeth.

00:05:03.530 --> 00:05:06.850
But the expression part

00:05:08.310 --> 00:05:13.470
comes through the Hamsa chakra, of all
these. So

00:05:15.670 --> 00:05:18.870
it's a very, very important thing

00:05:19.090 --> 00:05:26.590
in a Western mind

00:05:27.490 --> 00:05:31.330
to understand Hamsa chakra.

00:05:33.090 --> 00:05:38.530
There's a beautiful couplet about this in Sanskrit:

00:05:39.830 --> 00:05:44.090
"Hansa kshveta ha, baka ha kshveta
ha.

00:05:44.250 --> 00:05:47.570
Ko bhedo hansa bakayo ho.

00:05:47.790 --> 00:05:50.730
Neera-ksheera vivek e tu.

00:05:50.910 --> 00:05:54.190
Hansa ha hansaksh, baka ha baka
ha."

00:05:54.390 --> 00:06:00.790
Meaning: "The crane and the swan, both are white.

00:06:03.190 --> 00:06:06.810
And what makes the difference between the two?

00:06:08.210 --> 00:06:11.870
If you mix the water and the milk together,

00:06:13.250 --> 00:06:16.390
the hansa [swan, ed.] will just suck in the milk.

00:06:16.570 --> 00:06:20.690
So it can discriminate between the water and the milk.

00:06:20.890 --> 00:06:26.690
While the bakha, means the crane, cannot."

00:06:27.410 --> 00:06:32.150
The very significant thing for Sahaja yogis to understand.

00:06:34.630 --> 00:06:37.510
Discretion is to be understood

00:06:37.690 --> 00:06:40.530
very deeply within ourselves.

00:06:40.710 --> 00:06:43.910
And how we develop discretion

00:06:44.090 --> 00:06:47.750
is very important in Sahaja yoga.

00:06:48.450 --> 00:06:52.570
But before we go to that, let us see,

00:06:52.730 --> 00:06:59.350
how this discretion plays a part, very much,

00:07:02.670 --> 00:07:07.430
in the manifestation of our expressions out.

00:07:08.890 --> 00:07:13.330
We are the people, in the West, who always try

00:07:13.630 --> 00:07:16.910
to express ourselves outside.

00:07:17.970 --> 00:07:21.610
It's very important how you look.

00:07:22.530 --> 00:07:25.490
It's very important where you look.

00:07:25.650 --> 00:07:29.450
What you look, what you see.

00:07:29.710 --> 00:07:34.090
It's very important that

00:07:34.430 --> 00:07:37.610
your appearance should be good.

00:07:40.030 --> 00:07:43.930
Very particular, they spend lots of time in improving

00:07:44.110 --> 00:07:48.830
their appearances. This is the minimum.

00:07:49.830 --> 00:07:56.030
Then they have a method by which we call "the medias".

00:07:57.830 --> 00:08:02.910
The country speaks or manifests through the medias.

00:08:03.290 --> 00:08:06.530
And the medias have to have a training.

00:08:06.730 --> 00:08:09.730
Every country has it's specialty,

00:08:09.910 --> 00:08:13.730
one better than the other. And when you see all of them,

00:08:13.910 --> 00:08:17.890
you find that they lack discretion completely.

00:08:18.610 --> 00:08:22.450
Also in our speech,

00:08:24.250 --> 00:08:27.990
in our expression of literature,

00:08:28.790 --> 00:08:32.170
expression of poetry,

00:08:33.770 --> 00:08:38.370
expression of our relationships with others,

00:08:39.130 --> 00:08:44.030
any kind of expression requires discretion,

00:08:45.470 --> 00:08:50.570
which is a deep-seated knowledge or wisdom.

00:08:56.350 --> 00:09:02.790
If in the West people were not so much outside,

00:09:03.990 --> 00:09:07.110
they would have been much better off, I think.

00:09:10.970 --> 00:09:14.690
If, supposing, in England,

00:09:14.870 --> 00:09:19.810
people don't become punks,

00:09:20.870 --> 00:09:24.230
then others will laugh at them. And they'll think

00:09:24.410 --> 00:09:27.470
that, "This man has no money to become a punk."

00:09:27.630 --> 00:09:30.550
So kind of a fashion that sets in,

00:09:30.750 --> 00:09:35.130
in a society of that kind, which has no discretion

00:09:35.310 --> 00:09:38.650
and which is very outward.

00:09:38.850 --> 00:09:42.110
Fashions won't work out in countries, where they are

00:09:42.270 --> 00:09:45.890
deeply rooted into traditions

00:09:46.090 --> 00:09:49.310
and into proper understanding of life.

00:09:49.510 --> 00:09:53.530
Of course, the countries which have been very ancient,

00:09:53.710 --> 00:09:58.690
have been traditionally trying to improve themselves

00:09:59.310 --> 00:10:03.810
with "error and trial" and "error and trial" methods,

00:10:03.970 --> 00:10:06.930
have developed much better discretion.

00:10:07.090 --> 00:10:11.630
Much better understanding. But the countries which are

00:10:13.510 --> 00:10:17.630
not gone through all that ordeal, have not worked out,

00:10:17.830 --> 00:10:21.470
have not gone through that discipline, lack in discretion.

00:10:21.650 --> 00:10:24.650
And that's why many of the people,

00:10:24.830 --> 00:10:30.230
though they are of very deep seeking,

00:10:30.410 --> 00:10:33.410
have gone astray.

00:10:33.590 --> 00:10:36.670
If they had discretion, they would not have gone astray,

00:10:36.870 --> 00:10:39.830
they would not have gone to wrong places, but the discretion

00:10:39.970 --> 00:10:42.930
was missing.

00:10:43.390 --> 00:10:46.970
So it comes to the discretion, how to use

00:10:47.170 --> 00:10:50.470
your Ida nadi and Pingala nadi.

00:10:50.650 --> 00:10:54.970
And discretion to understand what is good and what is bad.

00:10:55.170 --> 00:10:59.250
Now let us see the Ida nadi.

00:11:00.730 --> 00:11:04.190
Ida nadi is very important,

00:11:04.370 --> 00:11:08.210
because the discretion in this can only come

00:11:08.390 --> 00:11:11.950
through traditional understanding.

00:11:12.370 --> 00:11:18.130
Ida Nadi starts from the Ganesha's point, Mooladhara.

00:11:18.890 --> 00:11:23.510
So first we miss the biggest support,

00:11:23.670 --> 00:11:27.550
the biggest help, the biggest nourishment

00:11:27.730 --> 00:11:31.650
of holiness and auspiciousness at Mooladhara,

00:11:31.830 --> 00:11:35.590
if we have no discretion.

00:11:35.770 --> 00:11:40.570
We always take to thing, which is detrimental to our growth,

00:11:40.750 --> 00:11:43.410
and also which may destroy us,

00:11:43.570 --> 00:11:46.210
not only us but the whole country.

00:11:46.390 --> 00:11:49.330
We like people who are destructive,

00:11:49.490 --> 00:11:53.330
when there is no discretion. Discretion means

00:11:53.510 --> 00:11:57.630
that you must choose the things which are good for you,

00:11:57.810 --> 00:12:01.550
which are benevolent to you, which are good for the collective,

00:12:01.730 --> 00:12:04.470
which are good for your ascent.

00:12:04.650 --> 00:12:09.250
On the contrary, the people who have no discretion

00:12:09.550 --> 00:12:15.790
fall into the traps of wrong type of people, like Freud.

00:12:17.110 --> 00:12:20.230
I mean to an Indian, Freud... nobody can believe that

00:12:20.410 --> 00:12:24.030
you can go into such a nonsensical idea.

00:12:24.910 --> 00:12:28.070
But people accepted Freud

00:12:28.270 --> 00:12:31.670
more than they could accept Christ.

00:12:32.370 --> 00:12:35.470
Because the discretion was completely missing.

00:12:35.650 --> 00:12:38.410
If they had that traditional discretion in them,

00:12:38.590 --> 00:12:42.970
they would have been saved. This [type?] traditional discretion

00:12:43.150 --> 00:12:46.270
is the thing that comes through Ida nadi.

00:12:46.450 --> 00:12:50.010
Now, that's what they people call it, as "conditioning".

00:12:50.210 --> 00:12:53.470
And they say that, "Conditioning is very bad. And people

00:12:53.630 --> 00:12:56.570
should not take to conditioning. And one should be free

00:12:56.750 --> 00:13:00.470
from conditioning." Which is absolutely
a wrong idea.

00:13:00.650 --> 00:13:03.810
In that also, there has to be discretion.

00:13:03.970 --> 00:13:07.370
What conditioning is good and what is not good

00:13:07.530 --> 00:13:10.610
has to be taken.

00:13:11.570 --> 00:13:16.850
Now, because there is no discretion about conditioning also,

00:13:17.030 --> 00:13:21.130
outright discarding all traditions, all that is

00:13:21.330 --> 00:13:26.150
coming to us through our experiences of our forefathers,

00:13:26.350 --> 00:13:29.950
everything is discarded. The history is discarded.

00:13:30.130 --> 00:13:33.910
And we say, "Oh, no, we are beyond it. We feel free."

00:13:34.110 --> 00:13:38.370
Like I was surprised, yesterday in the plane
somebody told me,

00:13:38.550 --> 00:13:43.310
"I feel very free when I have no clothes upon myself."

00:13:45.250 --> 00:13:48.290
I mean, if the clothes can imprison you,

00:13:48.470 --> 00:13:51.430
then what happens to the real prisons, what will they

00:13:51.590 --> 00:13:54.550
be for you?

00:13:54.730 --> 00:13:57.730
But that sort of a funny idea

00:13:57.910 --> 00:14:03.090
comes into the head of people and they think that,

00:14:03.370 --> 00:14:08.310
"We can justify all this stupidity that we follow,

00:14:08.490 --> 00:14:12.050
because we lack discretion."

00:14:12.410 --> 00:14:16.250
Intelligence cannot give you discretion.

00:14:18.310 --> 00:14:21.250
It cannot give you discretion as far as

00:14:21.430 --> 00:14:23.970
the conditioning is concerned.

00:14:24.150 --> 00:14:27.170
For a Sahaja yogi it is important to understand,

00:14:27.370 --> 00:14:31.390
how you develop your discretion.

00:14:31.570 --> 00:14:34.590
Yesterday only, I gave a very beautiful talk

00:14:34.770 --> 00:14:38.990
to the ladies of Paris or, I should say, ladies of France,

00:14:39.170 --> 00:14:43.770
regarding the discretion of women.

00:14:43.970 --> 00:14:48.490
The discretion of the Ida nadi is intuition.

00:14:49.490 --> 00:14:52.610
If you develop that discretion within you

00:14:52.770 --> 00:14:56.350
through your meditative powers,

00:14:56.550 --> 00:14:59.350
you develop intuition.

00:14:59.530 --> 00:15:03.730
And intuition is nothing but is the help of the Ganas,

00:15:03.890 --> 00:15:07.290
which are surrounding you.

00:15:07.470 --> 00:15:11.690
If you learn to take help from the Ganas,

00:15:11.870 --> 00:15:15.510
you can become very intuitive and

00:15:15.670 --> 00:15:20.890
without much intelligence of yours, you can say the right thing.

00:15:21.070 --> 00:15:25.670
The whole of Sahaja yoga, I would say,

00:15:25.850 --> 00:15:31.070
fifty percent at least out of that, is based on intuition.

00:15:32.570 --> 00:15:37.750
For that, you have to develop a proper sense of Shri Ganesh.

00:15:37.930 --> 00:15:42.310
Shri Ganesh in it's right sense you have to understand.

00:15:42.490 --> 00:15:45.890
From there it starts, because he is Ganapati. He is the one,

00:15:46.070 --> 00:15:49.750
who is the master, is the chief of all the Ganas.

00:15:49.930 --> 00:15:53.390
So the Ganas give you the intuition.

00:15:53.570 --> 00:15:56.570
For example,

00:15:58.230 --> 00:16:02.890
say, I have to go somewhere.

00:16:04.710 --> 00:16:07.810
And then I..., what I say is

00:16:08.010 --> 00:16:10.970
that, "No, I won't be able to go there tomorrow."

00:16:11.150 --> 00:16:14.150
And I won't go, somehow. And people think,

00:16:14.310 --> 00:16:18.290
"Mother, how do You know?" I know,

00:16:18.490 --> 00:16:22.350
because the Ganas are there, and what they say is the truth.

00:16:22.530 --> 00:16:24.930
They know all about it.

00:16:25.110 --> 00:16:30.590
Or anything I say about someone comes true.

00:16:31.250 --> 00:16:34.170
So they start asking me, "How is it Mother,

00:16:34.330 --> 00:16:37.610
You have come to know about it?" I live
on intuition.

00:16:37.790 --> 00:16:40.430
Like I have to catch a plane, I know by intuition what's going

00:16:40.610 --> 00:16:45.830
to happen. This part has to develop by worshiping Shri Ganesh.

00:16:46.010 --> 00:16:49.250
So imagine, Shri Ganesha also rules

00:16:49.450 --> 00:16:53.650
a part of the Hamsa chakra.

00:16:55.690 --> 00:17:00.450
So when we say Ham and Sa, these two are

00:17:00.650 --> 00:17:06.930
actually the bija mantras of the Agya.

00:17:08.030 --> 00:17:11.770
But when the Agya touches the Hamsa, it starts here.

00:17:11.970 --> 00:17:15.470
That's why at the base, at the root of it, is the Hamsa.

00:17:15.650 --> 00:17:20.130
And here the Ham, Ham means
"I am".

00:17:20.370 --> 00:17:23.930
If you are discrete, you will not take to fashions.

00:17:24.110 --> 00:17:28.590
You'll not take to stupid ideas. You have your own personality.

00:17:28.750 --> 00:17:31.890
You are a Sahaja yogi. You don't listen to people,

00:17:32.070 --> 00:17:35.090
who are non-Sahaja yogis.

00:17:35.250 --> 00:17:40.170
That is the Ham part:

00:17:40.870 --> 00:17:44.930
"I am". Not the ego part.

00:17:45.130 --> 00:17:48.630
But the Ham - to understand that, "I'm a Yogi

00:17:48.870 --> 00:17:53.850
and I know so many things, which normally people don't know,

00:17:54.010 --> 00:17:57.910
and so I have nothing to do with them.

00:17:59.510 --> 00:18:02.590
I've not to take any lessons from them.

00:18:02.770 --> 00:18:05.670
They are not to teach me anything.

00:18:05.830 --> 00:18:08.750
There's nothing that they know, I know much more."

00:18:08.930 --> 00:18:12.710
To be aware of your Self is Ham.

00:18:14.530 --> 00:18:19.150
So that comes from the right side, I would say.

00:18:19.330 --> 00:18:23.050
The discretion of right side is Ham

00:18:23.250 --> 00:18:27.010
and the discretion of left side is Sa.

00:18:27.190 --> 00:18:31.230
Sa means "You", means:

00:18:31.630 --> 00:18:35.330
"You are The One."

00:18:36.390 --> 00:18:39.770
In your case you know, who is the "You".

00:18:39.950 --> 00:18:45.230
But for every human being "You" is the Divine.

00:18:47.390 --> 00:18:51.010
"You are The One." This comes

00:18:51.170 --> 00:18:55.490
from the left side - is Sa.

00:18:56.250 --> 00:19:01.210
So the word "Hamsa" is made of two types of discretion,

00:19:01.370 --> 00:19:05.690
where to see "I am" and where to see "You are".

00:19:05.890 --> 00:19:09.570
On these two balances - as they have shown here beautifully -

00:19:09.730 --> 00:19:12.550
the Moon and the Sun.

00:19:12.730 --> 00:19:15.790
In the center is the cross,

00:19:15.950 --> 00:19:20.870
which gives you the balance, which gives you the dharma.

00:19:21.050 --> 00:19:24.070
How all these things are connected, one after another,

00:19:24.250 --> 00:19:27.190
layers after layers; you can see how

00:19:27.350 --> 00:19:31.010
dharma is connected with discretion.

00:19:31.190 --> 00:19:35.810
Now there are people who are

00:19:36.010 --> 00:19:40.050
suddenly enticed by some sort of a ritual.

00:19:40.230 --> 00:19:43.330
For example I've seen some Sahaja yogis,

00:19:43.510 --> 00:19:46.830
they come to the Puja and they are giving bandhan to them, like mad.

00:19:47.010 --> 00:19:49.610
On the way, they'll go, they'll give bandhan. Anywhere they go,

00:19:49.790 --> 00:19:53.010
they'll give bandhan, like mad.

00:19:54.430 --> 00:19:58.550
That's just conditioning. That's not discretion,

00:19:58.750 --> 00:20:01.550
that's not Sahaja yoga.

00:20:01.710 --> 00:20:05.190
It is to be seen - "Is it to be given bandhan or not?"

00:20:05.370 --> 00:20:07.550
In the presence of Mother there is bandhan,

00:20:07.750 --> 00:20:09.950
what is there to give bandhan to yourself?

00:20:10.130 --> 00:20:13.970
The people, when I'm talking, are giving
bandhan,

00:20:14.170 --> 00:20:19.690
raising their Kundalini. They're all mad people, I think.

00:20:19.910 --> 00:20:24.070
In the same way, there are people;

00:20:24.270 --> 00:20:27.210
Yesterday I heard there's one kind of a music record,

00:20:27.370 --> 00:20:30.290
is played everywhere in the ashrams,

00:20:30.470 --> 00:20:34.190
because they can all jump like on a camel.

00:20:34.370 --> 00:20:37.370
It's a music for the camels, you see.

00:20:37.550 --> 00:20:40.510
Now, this record everybody appreciates. Why?

00:20:40.710 --> 00:20:43.810
Because they can jump like a camel.

00:20:43.990 --> 00:20:47.310
Once you start jumping like a camel, human beings can't give up.

00:20:47.510 --> 00:20:50.930
They form habits. So they like that particular music.

00:20:51.070 --> 00:20:54.070
They'll go on jumping like a camel, because now they have become

00:20:54.270 --> 00:20:58.130
camels, they have to behave like camels. Now if there's something,

00:20:58.310 --> 00:21:01.390
some music, which is like a horse,

00:21:01.570 --> 00:21:05.970
like the trot maybe, maybe gallop, anything.

00:21:06.150 --> 00:21:09.130
Now, once they listen to it, suddenly they start following that

00:21:09.290 --> 00:21:13.170
rhythm. Now they become the horse, which is galloping.

00:21:13.450 --> 00:21:18.090
Now the horse is galloping, they become

00:21:18.250 --> 00:21:22.410
horses and they only like that galloping music.

00:21:22.610 --> 00:21:28.890
So on and so forth. Could be a donkey, could be anything.

00:21:29.610 --> 00:21:34.070
We are not animals, we are human beings and we are.

00:21:34.250 --> 00:21:37.330
Hum - "We are".

00:21:37.530 --> 00:21:41.710
We are Sahaja yogis, we are not dominated by any

00:21:41.910 --> 00:21:45.890
particular type of

00:21:46.190 --> 00:21:52.650
rhythm or particular type of music.

00:21:53.110 --> 00:21:56.050
Every variety we can appreciate and understand,

00:21:56.230 --> 00:21:59.690
as long as it is dharmic.

00:21:59.880 --> 00:22:02.840
As long as it is balancing.

00:22:03.030 --> 00:22:06.310
As long as it is auspicious and holy.

00:22:06.510 --> 00:22:12.610
So you can see on the Hamsa how many things are judged.

00:22:12.810 --> 00:22:16.330
I think, the whole of Sahaja yoga stands

00:22:16.510 --> 00:22:20.450
on the balance of Hamsa.

00:22:23.950 --> 00:22:27.850
There are people who are very

00:22:28.730 --> 00:22:33.130
astute, means very honest.

00:22:33.310 --> 00:22:38.830
But this honesty can go into a ridiculous limit.

00:22:41.450 --> 00:22:44.430
Or else , there are people,

00:22:44.590 --> 00:22:48.030
who are very hard working.

00:22:48.210 --> 00:22:51.410
This can also go to the ridiculous limit.

00:22:51.590 --> 00:22:55.830
So these qualities, which are supposed to be good,

00:22:57.070 --> 00:23:01.010
cannot be righteous.

00:23:01.250 --> 00:23:04.810
The righteousness is discretion.

00:23:08.610 --> 00:23:11.630
Glorified.

00:23:12.850 --> 00:23:15.730
If you have discretion,

00:23:15.910 --> 00:23:19.850
then you glorify

00:23:22.630 --> 00:23:26.070
that discretion into righteousness.

00:23:26.250 --> 00:23:30.990
Like, we can say now, Christ. We can take Christ.

00:23:31.190 --> 00:23:36.590
Christ was such a discretion.

00:23:37.810 --> 00:23:43.330
When Mary Magdalene was stoned,

00:23:43.910 --> 00:23:46.650
He had nothing to do with prostitutes, I mean,

00:23:46.810 --> 00:23:49.970
it's nothing to do at all, no relationship.

00:23:50.150 --> 00:23:53.330
But He could see in discretion that these people had no business

00:23:53.510 --> 00:23:56.890
to stone her. He stood up there,

00:23:57.070 --> 00:24:00.330
in His own courage, and he said that,

00:24:00.490 --> 00:24:04.170
"Those who are not committed any sin can

00:24:04.350 --> 00:24:07.110
throw the stone at [My/Me?]."

00:24:07.290 --> 00:24:10.230
This is the power of His discretion,

00:24:10.410 --> 00:24:15.470
that people just felt that discretion within themselves.

00:24:15.670 --> 00:24:19.230
And they felt that, "In discretion

00:24:19.450 --> 00:24:22.530
this man is a holy man

00:24:22.710 --> 00:24:26.310
and we cannot throw stones at Him".

00:24:26.490 --> 00:24:29.450
If you are discrete as Sahaja Yogis,

00:24:29.610 --> 00:24:33.790
you will make others discrete also.

00:24:33.970 --> 00:24:37.510
Others will have to be discrete and to understand.

00:24:37.690 --> 00:24:42.970
And this "Neera-Ksheera Vivek" is the differentiation

00:24:43.150 --> 00:24:46.630
between the water [neera, ed.] and the milk [ksheera, ed.].

00:24:46.830 --> 00:24:50.090
The bad and the good can come to you if you develop

00:24:50.270 --> 00:24:53.250
that discretion part.

00:24:56.250 --> 00:25:01.390
In Sahaja yoga, at every stage, you'll find people falter,

00:25:01.570 --> 00:25:04.810
also with the right side indiscretion.

00:25:05.010 --> 00:25:07.890
And the right side indiscretion comes from the ego

00:25:08.070 --> 00:25:11.510
manifestation of people.

00:25:11.810 --> 00:25:15.930
This ego is, as I said, is Ham.

00:25:16.110 --> 00:25:19.650
This ego doesn't work, when it has to work.

00:25:20.050 --> 00:25:24.970
For example, I find some people

00:25:25.170 --> 00:25:28.650
went for a marriage in the church.

00:25:28.850 --> 00:25:31.710
Of course, that's wrong for Sahaja yogis. We don't believe in any

00:25:31.890 --> 00:25:34.750
human religions, you know that. All right,

00:25:34.910 --> 00:25:37.490
you went to the church, is all right.

00:25:37.670 --> 00:25:40.750
But they sent a lady to London

00:25:40.910 --> 00:25:44.290
to buy "Laura Ashley" dresses.

00:25:47.210 --> 00:25:52.690
To buy. And I think, also, maybe, some men must be

00:25:52.870 --> 00:25:58.070
wearing tailcoats to do the wedding.

00:25:58.650 --> 00:26:01.950
Where is that ego lost?

00:26:02.150 --> 00:26:06.110
That ego that "you are the Sahaja yogi" was completely lost.

00:26:06.270 --> 00:26:09.190
I think, they all went for hairdressing,

00:26:09.350 --> 00:26:13.190
all kinds of things they did, and they all wanted to go there

00:26:13.370 --> 00:26:16.730
as old Christians,

00:26:16.910 --> 00:26:21.330
walking to the church next to the graves

00:26:21.510 --> 00:26:24.550
of stupid bishops.

00:26:26.430 --> 00:26:30.990
It's not only here, India is much worse.

00:26:31.190 --> 00:26:34.170
As far as religion is concerned, the left side,

00:26:34.330 --> 00:26:37.230
they are very, very conditioned people, and there they

00:26:37.410 --> 00:26:40.490
fail to understand, what is discretion.

00:26:40.670 --> 00:26:45.410
For example, we had Gyanadeva. He was such a great

00:26:45.590 --> 00:26:49.910
incarnation and He didn't even have shoes on His Feet!

00:26:50.070 --> 00:26:55.810
And these days, they are taking out a big procession of palanquin,

00:26:55.990 --> 00:27:00.550
so-called shoes in it - of Shri Gyanadeva -

00:27:00.730 --> 00:27:04.430
and thousands and thousands of people singing praise.

00:27:04.630 --> 00:27:07.470
Just imagine.

00:27:07.650 --> 00:27:11.110
Who can tell them that, "Gyanadeva had no shoes!

00:27:11.290 --> 00:27:14.650
What shoes are you carrying in the palanquin?"

00:27:14.830 --> 00:27:19.150
And whatever village they go, or whatever city they go,

00:27:19.310 --> 00:27:22.110
they are fed with sumptuous food;

00:27:22.290 --> 00:27:25.250
everybody falls at their feet, "The saints have come

00:27:25.430 --> 00:27:28.930
with a palanquin - " ...and the shoes never belonged

00:27:29.110 --> 00:27:34.230
to Gyanadeva in it! So this madness goes on.

00:27:34.430 --> 00:27:37.410
Now, you see all these things happening around you,

00:27:37.570 --> 00:27:40.570
in every country, in every religion, in every

00:27:40.750 --> 00:27:44.070
stupid area you see all this happening.

00:27:44.270 --> 00:27:47.410
But you just join hands!

00:27:48.810 --> 00:27:51.870
You become one with it!

00:27:56.930 --> 00:28:01.330
And then it becomes so difficult

00:28:01.530 --> 00:28:05.150
to understand, what has happened to you.

00:28:05.330 --> 00:28:10.930
Now, this Ego, when used properly,

00:28:11.270 --> 00:28:14.390
then it's discretion.

00:28:14.590 --> 00:28:18.990
Now also people have another very horrid, horrid conditioning,

00:28:19.170 --> 00:28:22.770
apart on the religion - is of the countries:

00:28:22.950 --> 00:28:26.310
"I belong to India", "I belong to Germany",

00:28:26.490 --> 00:28:31.490
"I belong to England." Everything is wretched.

